item.description:
A friend recently asked me: What do you use for vector search in Agent projects? I answered without hesitation: PostgreSQL + VectorChord.
He was surprised: &ldquo;Not Milvus, Pinecone, or other dedicated vector databases?&rdquo;
This made me realize many people misunderstand vector storage needs in the Agent era. Today I&rsquo;ll share why I only bet on PostgreSQL for Agent projects, how VectorChord achieves low-cost billion-scale vector retrieval, and its advantages over traditional HNSW approaches.
